  <prompt>
    Implement `IPlaybookCandidateSelector` + `PlaybookCandidateSelector` in `Services/Ai/Chat/` per FR-47 + FR-48. Wraps Phase B vector match output (task 112) + optional LLM rerank (task 111R). Decision tree uses constants `confidenceThreshold = 0.85`, `secondaryThreshold = 0.80`, `confidenceDeltaMargin = 0.05` defined in `RoutingOptions` (typed options per ADR-018). FR-48 invariant: result is ALWAYS surfaced as candidates â€” NEVER auto-execute even on a high-confidence single match. Wire into `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` so the file-aware path emits `playbook_options` for FE confirmation.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat-routing decision logic, ADR-018 typed options, and Spaarke FR-48 user-confirmation invariant.</role>

  <goal>
    A new `IPlaybookCandidateSelector.SelectAsync(userMessage, attachmentMetadata, vectorMatches, ct)` returning `IReadOnlyList&lt;PlaybookCandidate&gt;` (top-3 above secondaryThreshold). Decision tree implements (a) confident vector-only path (no LLM call) and (b) ambiguous rerank path (1 LLM call via 111R). `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` is updated so the file-aware branch returns candidates for FE confirmation â€” never auto-executes. Unit tests cover all branches; integration test for `playbook_options` SSE shape lands in 117a/117b.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 5R revised scope (spec.md Â§"Phase 5+7 Revised Scope"). FR-46 hybrid reranker lives in 111R; this task is the orchestrator. FR-47 defines top-N rules. FR-48 is the user-confirmation invariant: no path through `DispatchAsync` (slash or NL) may auto-execute when files are attached â€” both must emit `playbook_options`. The selector is the decision point.
    </background>
