  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read 111R outputs (`IIntentRerankerService` interface + `RerankerResult` DTO) and existing `PlaybookDispatcher.cs` Phase B vector match wiring. Confirm shape of vector-match output (ordered list with embedding scores).</step>
    <step order="2">Add constants to `RoutingOptions` (typed options per ADR-018): `ConfidenceThreshold = 0.85`, `SecondaryThreshold = 0.80`, `ConfidenceDeltaMargin = 0.05`. Bind to `Routing` config section; add DataAnnotations `[Range(0,1)]` validation.</step>
    <step order="3">Design `IPlaybookCandidateSelector` interface: `Task&lt;CandidateSelectionResult&gt; SelectAsync(string userMessage, IReadOnlyList&lt;AttachmentMetadata&gt; attachments, IReadOnlyList&lt;VectorMatch&gt; vectorMatches, CancellationToken ct)`. Result includes `Candidates`, `RerankInvoked`, `Reason`.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement decision tree in `PlaybookCandidateSelector`:
      (a) IF top-1 score &gt;= ConfidenceThreshold AND (top-2 score is null OR (top-1 - top-2) &gt; ConfidenceDeltaMargin) â†’ return top-3 above SecondaryThreshold; do NOT invoke reranker.
      (b) ELSE â†’ invoke `IIntentRerankerService.RerankAsync` with top-5; reranker returns top-3 of top-5.
      (c) IF fewer than 3 candidates above SecondaryThreshold â†’ return whatever matches (could be 0, 1, or 2).
    </step>
    <step order="5">Register `IPlaybookCandidateSelector` in `AiServicesModule` unconditionally (CLAUDE.md Â§10 F.1 asymmetric-registration prevention).</step>
    <step order="6">Wire into `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` file-aware branch: replace any direct vector-match-only dispatch logic with `_selector.SelectAsync(...)`. The dispatcher returns candidates for FE rendering â€” NEVER auto-executes a single high-confidence match (FR-48). Slash path and NL path both flow through the same selector.</step>
    <step order="7">Add unit tests `PlaybookCandidateSelectorTests` covering each FR-47 branch:
      (a) High-confidence single (top-1=0.95, top-2=0.70) â†’ top-3 returned, no rerank invoked.
      (b) High-confidence but close (top-1=0.90, top-2=0.88) â†’ rerank invoked.
      (c) Low confidence (top-1=0.78) â†’ rerank invoked.
      (d) Fewer than 3 above 0.80 â†’ return whatever matches.
      (e) Empty vector matches â†’ empty result.
    </step>
    <step order="8">Add `PlaybookDispatcherTests` case asserting FR-48 invariant: file-aware path with single high-confidence match returns candidates (does NOT execute the playbook). Mock `IPlaybookExecutionEngine` and verify `ExecuteAsync` is NOT called from `DispatchAsync` file-aware branch.</step>
    <step order="9">Grep `Services/Ai/Chat/` for any remaining auto-execute path on the file-aware branch; confirm only the FE-triggered `/execute` endpoint (117a/117b) calls `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync` for file-aware dispatches.</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. All tests pass.</step>
    <step order="11">Measure BFF publish size; report compressed delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline; expect &lt;1 MB delta. code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates).</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 113R â†’ âś…; current-task.md â†’ ready for 117a.</step>
  </steps>

